definitions.definition: ( chemistry ) a molecule containing a silicon atom which forms a double bond
( organic chemistry ) an organosilene , a molecule containing a silicon atom doubly bonded to a carbon atom
( inorganic chemistry ) a silicon analog of alkenes containing at least one silicon-silicon double bond .

main_definition: ( chemistry ) a molecule containing a silicon atom which forms a double bond
secondary_definitions: ( organic chemistry ) an organosilene , a molecule containing a silicon atom doubly bonded to a carbon atom

definitions.definition: Any of several plants of the genus Silene .

main_definition: ( botany ) Any of several plants of the genus Silene .
